<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-114] exception when a node is joining</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-114</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a new node is joining, StorageService is notified and the log shows this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: &quot;T&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
        at java.lang.NumberFormatException.forInputString(Unknown Source)&lt;br/&gt;
        at java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Unknown Source)&lt;br/&gt;
        at java.math.BigInteger.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(Unknown Source)&lt;br/&gt;
        at java.math.BigInteger.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(Unknown Source)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.cassandra.dht.RandomPartitioner$3.fromString(RandomPartitioner.java:97)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.cassandra.service.StorageService.onChange(StorageService.java:646)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.cassandra.gms.Gossiper.doNotifications(Gossiper.java:770)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.cassandra.gms.Gossiper.handleNewJoin(Gossiper.java:644)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my case, the EndPointState had a nodeIdState who&apos;s state_ was &quot;Token(165385238122940489124770581854348071118)&quot; and produced the exception.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
